message.body: Up to 5 different inputs can be executed at the same time by using + to combine inputs. message.body: Normal duration of inputs is 8 frames. You can separate multiple inputs by using spaces or commas to execute multiple inputs in rapid succession.

message.body: Example: Up+Right+Square;120 X+O+Down;60 *5 Will pull Up and Right on the Left Analog Stick and press the Square Button for 120 frames (2 seconds), then press the X and O Buttons and pull Down on the Left Analog Stick for 60 frames (1 second), and *5 means the input will be executed once, then it will be repeated 5 times. There is no delay between inputs.

message.body: There is no delay between inputs, but sometimes you'll need a delay between inputs, you can use Wait or Stop to add a delay between inputs. message.body: Up to 5 different inputs can be executed at the same time by using + to combine inputs. Commands are NOT case sensitive: left and lEft will both pull Left on the Left Analog Stick.

message.body: Example: Up+Right+Square;120 X+O+Down;60 *5 Will pull Up and Right on the Left Analog Stick and press the Square Button for 120 frames (2 seconds), then press the X and O Buttons and pull Down on the Left Analog Stick for 60 frames (1 second), and *5 means the input will be executed once, then it will be repeated 5 times. There is no delay between inputs.
